					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No one has really started it yet.  Just to review what's needed if a relay computer isn't used:
<br />
<br />Hardware- basic (for me), I could hook up an ISA ethernet card in a couple minutes
<br />
<br />UDP-  somewhat easy, can include stuff like DHCP without too much extra work
<br />
<br />TCP-  INSANELY HARD!  A cut down TCP stack would be barely possible with the amount of ram available.  Stuff like reordering and reconstructing packets gets really messy.  Could be ripped out of ContikiOS.</div>

